         <div type="commentary" subtype="linebyline">
            <list>
               <item corresp="#lb3" xml:space="preserve"><ref>1-2</ref> <p><emph rend="italics">glaucoma</emph> before <emph rend="italics">staphyloma</emph> also in P.Ross.Georg. 1.20; Gal. <emph rend="italics">DM</emph> 344-5 (19.435.13-6 K) and Ps.-Sor. <emph rend="italics">Quaest.med.</emph> 362-3 (MS Lincol. 220, f. 41r). On <emph rend="italics">glaucoma</emph>, cf. <listBibl><bibl><ref target="http://papyri.info/biblio/53246">Marganne 1979</ref></bibl></listBibl>, 199-214.</p></item>
               <item corresp="#lb4" xml:space="preserve"><ref>3</ref> <p>For the question, cf. P.Ross.Georg. 1.20.68-9.
τόπο(ν) is abbreviated with an overline.</p></item>
               <item corresp="#lb6" xml:space="preserve"><ref>4-5</ref> <p>Cf. P.Ross.Georg. 1.20.70-2; Ps.-Gal. <emph rend="italics">DM</emph> 345 and 349 (19.435.15-6 and 439.13-4 K). For the comparison with grape (e.g. Aët. 7.36 [CMG 8.2, 286.18-20 Oliv.]), cf. <ref target="http://www.papirologia.unipr.it/CPGM/biblio.html#skoda1988">Skoda 1988</ref>, 286 s.v. πτερύγιον. 
The final alpha of σταφύλωμα seem to extend to the right in a sort of short line filler.</p></item>
               <item corresp="#lb7" xml:space="preserve"><ref>6</ref> <p>Etiological question as in P.Ross.Georg. 1.20.73-4.</p></item>
               <item corresp="#lb11" xml:space="preserve"><ref>7-10</ref> <p>Text restored combining P.Ross.Georg. 1.20.75-9 and Paul.Aeg. 6.19 (CMG 9.2, 59.8-10 Heib.).</p></item>
               <item corresp="#lb13" xml:space="preserve"><ref>11-2</ref> <p>Question introducing different <emph rend="italics">staphylomata</emph> according to size and colour (cf. P.Ross.Georg. 1.20.80-1).</p></item>
               <item corresp="#lb16" xml:space="preserve"><ref>15</ref> <p>For the surgery of <emph rend="italics">staphyloma</emph>, cf. e.g. Aët. 7.37 (CMG 8.2, 288.7-289.20 Oliv.); Paul.Aeg. 6.19 (CMG 9.2, 59.12-20 Heib.); Cels. 7.7.11 (CML 1.318.26-319.2 Marx).</p></item>
               <item corresp="#lb18" xml:space="preserve"><ref>16-7</ref> <p>Poss. description of the surgical procedures modeled upon Aët. 7.37 (CMG 8.2, 288.9-11 Oliv.) .</p></item>
            </list>
